{
  "name": "Poison Touch Hex",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "systems/pf1/icons/skills/violet_02.jpg",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>The witch empowers herself or an ally within 30 feet with poisonous nails. The affected creature gains a claw attack as a secondary attack that deals 1d3 points of damage (1d2 for Small creatures) and has the following poison ability:</p><fieldset><legend>Witch Toxin</legend><p>Claw—injury; save Fort DC 10 + half the witch’s level + the witch’s Intelligence modifier; frequency 1/round for 6 rounds; effect 1d2 Str; cure 1 save.</p></fieldset><p>The creature gains this claw attack for a number of minutes equal to the witch’s level. If the target already has a claw attack, that attack gains the poison ability listed above, but the DC is 1 higher.</p><p>Once a creature has benefited from this hex, it cannot benefit from it again for 24 hours.</p>"
    },
